Java Basics for Beginners
1. What is Java?

Java is a high-level, object-oriented programming language developed by Sun Microsystems (now owned by Oracle Corporation).

Features of Java
Platform Independent (Write Once, Run Anywhere)
Object-Oriented
Secure
Robust
Portable
Multithreaded

Java code runs on the JVM, allowing the same program to work on different operating systems.

2. JDK, JRE, and JVM
JVM (Java Virtual Machine)
Executes Java bytecode.
Converts bytecode into machine code.
JRE (Java Runtime Environment)
Contains JVM + libraries needed to run Java programs.
JDK (Java Development Kit)
Contains JRE + development tools like compiler.
Required for writing and developing Java applications.
Simple Formula
JDK = JRE + Development Tools
JRE = JVM + Libraries

3. First Java Program
public class HelloWorld {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello World");
    }
}
Output
Hello World
Explanation
Keyword	Meaning
public	Accessible everywhere
class	Blueprint of an object
HelloWorld	Class name
static	Method belongs to class
void	Returns nothing
main()	Starting point of program
System.out.println()	Prints output
